==English==
===Noun===
# {{AU}} A [[tax avoidance]] scheme from the 1970s.
#: 1982: ''The 'bottom of the harbour' scheme was so named because a company once stripped of its assets, was dumped and, like a body in a cement suit, sank never to be seen again.''<!-- the commas here look wrongly placed, but are in fact as shown in Wilkes --> &mdash; [[w:Sydney Morning Herald|Sydney Morning Herald]], 5 June 1982, page 13.  Quoted in G. A. Wilkes, ''A Dictionary of Australian Colloquialisms'', second edition, 1985, [[w:Sydney University Press|Sydney University Press]], ISBN 0-424-00113-6.